<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xml>
  <file>
    <title>Do_block_smoothing</title>
    <breadcumbs>
      <link file="BitMiracle_LibJpeg_Classic.xml">
        <text>BitMiracle.LibJpeg.Classic namespace</text>
      </link>
      <text> :: </text>
      <link file="jpeg_decompress_struct.xml">
        <text>jpeg_decompress_struct</text>
      </link>
    </breadcumbs>
    <descriptionarticle only="false">
      <text>Apply interblock smoothing in early stages of decoding progressive JPEG files.</text> </descriptionarticle>
    <seealso>
      <ref caption="Decompression parameter selection" file="Classic\Decompression_parameter_selection.xml" />
    </seealso>
    <signature>
      <property access="full">
        <name>Do_block_smoothing</name>
        <return type="Boolean">
          <p>
            <text>If </text> <b><text>true</text> </b><text>, interblock smoothing is applied in early stages of decoding progressive JPEG files; if </text> <b><text>false</text> </b><text>, not. Early progression stages look "fuzzy" with smoothing, "blocky" without.</text> </p>
          <p>
            <text>Default value: </text> <b><text>true</text> </b></p>
        </return>
      </property>
    </signature>
    <remarks>
      <text>In any case, block smoothing ceases to be applied after the first few AC coefficients are known to full accuracy, so it is relevant only when using </text> <link file="Classic/Buffered_image_mode.xml"><text>buffered-image mode</text> </link><text> for progressive images.</text> </remarks>
  </file>
</xml>